A building contractor was yesterday docked before an Ikeja magistrate court, Lagos, for allegedly stealing a sum of N4.8 million belonging to Bishmur Company Limited, Lagos. The police told the court that the accused person, Adesina Ojumu, 39, committed the offence on April 11, 2019 at No. 55, Karimu-Laka Street, Egbeda, Lagos. The police prosecutor, Sergeant Mike Umar, alleged that Ojumu obtained the money, property of Bishmur Company Limited, from Lasisi Olayiwola under the pretence of constructing 219 aluminium windows for the company. Ojumu pleaded not guilty to the two criminal charges levelled against him. Chief Magistrate A. A. Fashola ordered the accused person to be remanded in police custody and adjourned the case till September 16, 2019. Businessman to face trial for allegedly stealing $123,000 Police arraign man, 21, over theft, unlawful display of arms Data analyst charged with stealing human hair Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin